LINUX COMMANDS:-

id - to checkt he identity
pwd - to check the present or current working directory
default user - ec2-user
sudo -i or sudo su -  - to convert the default to root user

hardware commands:-

cat /etc/passwd  - to cechk the userlist
cat /proc/cpuinfo  or lscpu  - to check the cpu information
cat /proc/meminfo  or lsmem  - to chck the memory infomation
cat /etc/os-release          - to give the os(amazon-machine-image) information
uname -a  - to cehck the kernel version of os(operating system)

basic commands:-

ll    - to check the longlist files
ls    - to check the short files
ls -l - to check the lsit of all files
ls -al - to chek the hidden files
ls -lsh - to check the size of the files
ls -ltr - to check the latest files
mkdir directory - to create a directory or folder
cd              - to change the directory path
touch filename  - to create a filename
tree   - to check the tree workflow of  directory and files

note: drwx-- directory it indicates blue colur 
      -rw--r- file  it indicates white colour

